## Project Overview

Sovereign Watch is a self-hosted, distributed Multi-INT fusion platform that
ingests and visualizes real-time aviation (ADS-B), maritime (AIS), orbital
(TLE/SGP4), RF infrastructure, and internet infrastructure data on a WebGL
tactical map.

Stack:
- Frontend: TypeScript · React 18.2 · Vite 7.3 · Deck.gl 9.0 · MapLibre/Mapbox
- Backend API: Python 3.11 · FastAPI · asyncpg · LiteLLM · Redis · aiokafka
- Database: TimescaleDB (PostgreSQL 16 + PostGIS + pgvector)
- Message bus: Redpanda (Kafka-compatible)
- Runtime: Docker Compose — all services containerised

## Directory Map

```
frontend/src/
  components/map/        — Deck.gl + MapLibre/Mapbox map components
  components/layouts/    — HUD shell, sidebars, top bar
  components/js8call/    — HF radio terminal UI
  layers/                — Deck.gl layer definitions
  hooks/                 — Custom React hooks
  workers/               — Web workers (compute-heavy tasks)
  types.ts               — Shared TypeScript types

backend/api/
  routers/               — FastAPI route handlers (tracks, analysis, orbital, rf, infra, system)
  services/              — Business logic (historian, tak, broadcast, schema_context)
  models/schemas.py      — Pydantic request/response models
  core/config.py         — Settings (env vars via pydantic-settings)
  core/database.py       — asyncpg pool + Redis client

backend/ingestion/
  aviation_poller/       — ADS-B ingest (adsb.fi, adsb.lol, airplanes.live)
  maritime_poller/       — AIS ingest (AISStream WebSocket)
  orbital_pulse/         — TLE fetch + SGP4 propagation
  rf_pulse/              — RF repeaters + NOAA weather radio
  infra_poller/          — Internet outages + submarine cables
```

## Architectural Rules

1. **Container-first**: All services run in Docker Compose. Do not run the app
   outside containers. Lint and unit tests may run on the host.

2. **TAK Protocol**: All inter-service messages use the TAK Protocol (simplified
   CoT serialised as JSON). See `Documentation/TAK_Protocol.md`.

3. **Deck.gl layer ordering**: ALWAYS read `agent_docs/z-ordering.md` before
   modifying any map layer. Incorrect z-order causes invisible layers or WebGL
   depth conflicts that are hard to debug.

4. **Ingestion pollers require rebuild**: Changes to any file in
   `backend/ingestion/` require `docker compose up -d --build <poller-name>`.
   Hot reload is NOT available for pollers.

5. **AI analyst schema**: The LiteLLM-based analyst in
   `backend/api/routers/analysis.py` uses `services/schema_context.py` to
   inject field definitions and anomaly indicators into LLM prompts. Update
   that file when adding new track fields or entity types.

6. **LSP tooling**: `pyrightconfig.json` (Python) and `frontend/tsconfig.json`
   (TypeScript) are at project root / frontend/. `.vscode/settings.json` is
   pre-configured — no additional LSP setup needed for VS Code family editors.

## Key Commands

```bash
# Frontend — hot reload active at http://localhost (via nginx)
cd frontend && npm run lint
cd frontend && npm run test

# Backend API — hot reload active (uvicorn --reload)
cd backend/api && ruff check .
cd backend/api && python -m pytest

# Any ingestion poller change
docker compose up -d --build sovereign-adsb-poller   # example

# Full stack
docker compose up -d --build
docker compose logs -f sovereign-backend
```

## Code Style

- Python: ruff enforced (no explicit config — uses pyproject defaults). 4-space indent.
- TypeScript: ESLint flat config (`frontend/eslint.config.js`) + Prettier.
  2-space indent. Strict mode enabled in `tsconfig.json`.
- Imports: absolute paths in Python, relative in TypeScript components.

